CHANGELOG.md:617:- Added depth-2 sampler-effects end-to-end test coverage (frac-0113): `tests/test_sampler_effects.py` now includes `SamplerEffectsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `sw_sampler_fx` SuperCollider source and SC-side runtime harness through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts bus/control defaults (`in_bus=16`, `out_bus=0`, delay/reverb/freeze/comb controls), verifies the ordered integrated FX chain (`In.ar` -> `DelayC.ar` -> `FreeVerb.ar` -> `PV_Freeze` -> `CombC.ar` -> `LPF.ar` -> `Out.ar`), confirms the runtime harness compiles `sampler_effects.scd`, toggles `freeze_amount`, exercises `comb_decay` / `comb_damping`, runs `runImpulseComb`, checks the 61.74 Hz comb target, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic. `tests/test_test_sampler_effects_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing SuperCollider behavior remains unchanged because the source already produced the required one-path FX chain; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4663 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:725:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:747:- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:803:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:896:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
CHANGELOG.md:897:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:898:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
